column1: Data compilation used in calculation of N budget, organized by year of publication.

Geologic Setting abbreviations:  O = Oceanic; C = Continental; S = Sediment; L = Lithosphere; A = altered (<300°C); M = metamorphosed (>300 °C); M = primary mantle volcanics; X = xenoliths; OIB = Ocean Isl_and_ Basalt; VV= Volcanic volatiles
Rock name abbreviations: BIF = b_and_ed iron formation; MORB = mid-ocean ridge basalt; OIB = ocean isl_and_ basalt; F = fluid; G = gas

Columns show, in order, References/notes, Sample name as used in original study, geologic setting (assigned by us), rock type (after original study), Age (Ga), δ15N _and_ error, N concentration (ppm), δ 13 C, Yb, Lu, _and_ Rb concentration (ppm), K2O (wt. %), _and_ Ar data where available
Full references are in the Supplementary References document.
